Do you have any proof?

257
00:14:12,547 --> 00:14:16,347
We can probably find out by checking the hotel parking lot.

258
00:14:16,347 --> 00:14:18,747
Your husband, who headed home,

259
00:14:18,747 --> 00:14:20,547
had to come alone to the parking lot

260
00:14:20,547 --> 00:14:22,647
or the crime couldn't have been committed!

261
00:14:22,647 --> 00:14:25,047
That's why, it should still be there!

262
00:14:25,047 --> 00:14:29,347
The car that your husband drove to the hotel in!

263
00:14:29,347 --> 00:14:30,947
Because if your husband used his lover's car

264
00:14:30,947 --> 00:14:32,547
to go in and out of the hotel,

265
00:14:32,547 --> 00:14:35,947
you would never have chosen the parking lot to commit the crime,

266
00:14:35,947 --> 00:14:40,347
not wanting to risk your face being seen.

267
00:14:40,347 --> 00:14:44,447
The garage here only has space for one car.

268
00:14:44,447 --> 00:14:48,347
Most likely, your husband rented a car behind your back.

269
00:14:48,347 --> 00:14:52,347
Then, why not investigate it? That hotel parking lot!

270
00:14:53,447 --> 00:14:55,847
And, should you not find a car like that,

271
00:14:55,847 --> 00:14:57,247
I will not, despite it being you, attorney at law, Kisaki

272
00:14:57,247 --> 00:15:00,347
-get away with it. -Say!

273
00:15:00,347 --> 00:15:02,947
Mrs. Arisawa, you're really good at judo, right?

274
00:15:02,947 --> 00:15:06,247
-What? -Wait, Conan!

275
00:15:06,247 --> 00:15:09,647
Could you teach me the inner thigh throw?

276
00:15:09,647 --> 00:15:12,547
That's when you use your opponent's attacking power

277
00:15:12,547 --> 00:15:14,947
to your advantage and throw them, right?

278
00:15:14,947 --> 00:15:17,447
You use their power to throw them to the ground

279
00:15:17,447 --> 00:15:18,847
and gain points, right?

280
00:15:18,847 --> 00:15:22,347
Using your opponent's power to your advantage...

281
00:15:22,347 --> 00:15:24,447
Geez! What are you up to?

282
00:15:24,447 --> 00:15:25,747
But back then,

283
00:15:25,747 --> 00:15:30,947
didn't Mrs. Arisawa teach us how to adjust our seats?

284
00:15:30,947 --> 00:15:33,247
You know how to adjust the seat, don't you?

285
00:15:33,247 --> 00:15:34,547
There's a lever on the right side of the seat.

286
00:15:34,547 --> 00:15:36,047
And if you pull it...

287
00:15:36,047 --> 00:15:39,147
See, like this, the seat will move.

288
00:15:39,947 --> 00:15:41,447
I see.

289
00:15:41,447 --> 00:15:46,047
The car that you ended up driving us back in...

290
00:15:46,047 --> 00:15:49,447
That was the car your husband drove to the hotel, was it not?

291
00:15:50,547 --> 00:15:56,147
That's why you demonstrated how to adjust the seat, right?

292
00:15:56,147 --> 00:15:58,447
Your husband is smaller and shorter than you.

293
00:15:58,447 --> 00:16:01,247
It's natural for his seat to be in a different position.

294
00:16:01,247 --> 00:16:06,847
Should you adjust it on a whim, it would look suspicious.

295
00:16:06,847 --> 00:16:08,147
That's right.

296
00:16:08,147 --> 00:16:12,147
That would also explain your adjusting of the rear-view mirror.

297
00:16:12,147 --> 00:16:15,047
Which means it should come as no surprise

298
00:16:15,047 --> 00:16:18,447
why you couldn't find the car in the parking lot.

299
00:16:18,447 --> 00:16:21,747
Most likely, you trailed him closely

300
00:16:21,747 --> 00:16:25,047
and avoided letting him take notice of you.

301
00:16:25,047 --> 00:16:26,447
You probably got into the car

302
00:16:26,447 --> 00:16:29,647
at the same time your husband got on and strangled him.

303
00:16:29,647 --> 00:16:33,947
Afterwards, you most likely rushed back full speed to the restaurant.

304
00:16:34,847 --> 00:16:36,547
And, due to this, you didn't have enough time

305
00:16:36,547 --> 00:16:39,647
to remember the car position, right?

306
00:16:39,647 --> 00:16:42,547
If you think about it, it's really a strange story.

307
00:16:42,547 --> 00:16:46,147
Your reason for inviting us to that hotel

308
00:16:46,147 --> 00:16:48,747
was because you could get a discount for parking.

309
00:16:48,747 --> 00:16:53,547
Then, you should've shown the ticket when you paid the parking fee.

310
00:16:53,547 --> 00:16:55,347
Despite not having gone anywhere else,

311
00:16:55,347 --> 00:16:58,847
the ticket was suspiciously missing.

312
00:16:58,847 --> 00:17:01,247
This is peculiar, isn't it?

313
00:17:01,247 --> 00:17:04,047
When you said you had lost the ticket, what you really meant was

314
00:17:04,047 --> 00:17:08,347
that you weren't sure where your husband put it, right?

315
00:17:08,347 --> 00:17:11,447
If your husband were the type to put things away at random,

316
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:13,247
it could be behind the sun visor

317
00:17:13,247 --> 00:17:15,547
or even in the ashtray.

318
00:17:15,547 --> 00:17:17,747
With a proper search of the car,

319
00:17:17,747 --> 00:17:19,247
I imagine we'll find it.

320
00:17:19,247 --> 00:17:23,247
The hotel parking ticket with your husband's fingerprints on it.

321
00:17:23,247 --> 00:17:25,247
That would be proof that

322
00:17:25,247 --> 00:17:28,847
your husband was also at the hotel tonight.

323
00:17:28,847 --> 00:17:31,347
Well, if we check the trunk,

324
00:17:31,347 --> 00:17:35,247
we should find evidence that he was moved from there.

325
00:17:35,247 --> 00:17:36,847
Maybe his hair

326
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:40,247
and possibly even the tie used as a weapon,

327
00:17:40,247 --> 00:17:41,947
as well as his shoes.

328
00:17:41,947 --> 00:17:46,347
And as for the shoes that we saw at the front entrance tonight,

329
00:17:46,347 --> 00:17:49,147
those were likely prepared by you.

330
00:17:49,147 --> 00:17:52,547
Now, before the police come across this evidence,

331
00:17:52,547 --> 00:17:54,247
hurry and turn yourself in.

332
00:17:54,247 --> 00:17:57,147
-The sock on his left foot... -What?

333
00:17:57,147 --> 00:17:58,947
I just remembered.

334
00:17:58,947 --> 00:18:02,947
That's where my husband usually puts his parking tickets.

335
00:18:02,947 --> 00:18:05,547
So if they check there, they should find it.

336
00:18:05,547 --> 00:18:08,247
Then, Yuko really did...

337
00:18:08,247 --> 00:18:09,747
But why?

338
00:18:09,747 --> 00:18:14,347
How could someone like you esort to murder over a mere affair?

339
00:18:14,347 --> 00:18:18,347
If it were only an affair, a divorce would have sufficed,

340
00:18:18,347 --> 00:18:21,747
but the other woman was Kajimoto's wife.

341
00:18:21,747 --> 00:18:23,847
I just couldn't allow it.

342
00:18:23,847 --> 00:18:25,447
Mr. Kajimoto...

343
00:18:25,447 --> 00:18:28,047
That's the gold medallist you mentioned before, right?

344
00:18:28,047 --> 00:18:31,947
But wouldn't that give you even mere reason to work it out?

345
00:18:31,947 --> 00:18:35,047
It isn't like you weren't acquainted with his wife.

346
00:18:35,047 --> 00:18:37,147
Yeah, my husband and I

347
00:18:37,147 --> 00:18:40,747
visited Kajimoto's house often in the past.

348
00:18:40,747 --> 00:18:44,047
Such a good wife, such a cute child...

349
00:18:44,047 --> 00:18:46,947
They were the ideal family you see in pictures.

350
00:18:46,947 --> 00:18:49,347
But my husband ruined it!

351
00:18:52,247 --> 00:18:55,647
When I considered the suffering that was to come,

352
00:18:55,647 --> 00:18:58,247
I couldn't live on that way.

353
00:18:58,247 --> 00:19:00,747
Not even a divorce would've been enough!

354
00:19:01,747 --> 00:19:05,247
Right. I never should've gotten close.

355
00:19:05,247 --> 00:19:08,447
If only we never visited Mr. Kajimoto's house,

356
00:19:08,447 --> 00:19:11,947
my husband and his wife wouldn't have met.

357
00:19:11,947 --> 00:19:13,947
If only I had kept my admiration to myself,

358
00:19:13,947 --> 00:19:17,147
none of this would have come to be.

359
00:19:17,147 --> 00:19:20,847
This is merely an assumption.

360
00:19:20,847 --> 00:19:24,947
Could it be that your husband just wanted more attention from you?

361
00:19:24,947 --> 00:19:27,747
-What? -The tape trick for an alibi

362
00:19:27,747 --> 00:19:29,347
would have only worked two, maybe three times.

363
00:19:29,347 --> 00:19:30,847
After that, it doesn't work anymore.

364
00:19:30,847 --> 00:19:35,047
And, when it comes to those matches from the restaurant...

365
00:19:35,047 --> 00:19:38,547
He may as well have told you directly that he went there often.

366
00:19:38,547 --> 00:19:40,247
Are you saying my husband

367
00:19:40,247 --> 00:19:42,347
deliberately wanted me to think he was having an affair?

368
00:19:42,347 --> 00:19:44,947
Yes. He was jealous

369
00:19:44,947 --> 00:19:48,447
that you still thought of Mr. Kajimoto despite being married.

370
00:19:48,447 --> 00:19:51,247
That can't be...

371
00:19:51,247 --> 00:19:55,847
But he crossed the line and angered you, caught fire,

372
00:19:55,847 --> 00:19:57,747
and plunged to his death.

373
00:19:57,747 --> 00:20:02,147
Maybe the sun that burned Icarus's wings

374
00:20:02,147 --> 00:20:04,747
was actually you.

375
00:20:09,647 --> 00:20:12,347
-It was all thanks to Dad! -What?

376
00:20:12,347 --> 00:20:15,047
You know, the alibi tapes!

377
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:17,047
A coincidence! Just a coincidence!

378
00:20:17,047 --> 00:20:18,747
Definitely an accidental hit!

379
00:20:18,747 --> 00:20:20,947
Was it really a coincidence?

380
00:20:20,947 --> 00:20:25,847
What if it was a deliberate hint just for Mom?

381
00:20:25,847 --> 00:20:28,847
No way.

382
00:20:28,847 --> 00:20:31,447
He was probably too embarrassed to say anything!

383
00:20:31,447 --> 00:20:33,147
Is that so?

384
00:20:33,147 --> 00:20:35,547
If you want to find out, here's the phone!

385
00:20:36,847 --> 00:20:40,747
Well, I should at least inform him that the case is over.

386
00:20:43,847 --> 00:20:45,347
It's me.

387
00:20:45,347 --> 00:20:47,447
About the case...

388
00:20:50,247 --> 00:20:53,047
Sorry, I'm still playing mahjong.

389
00:20:53,047 --> 00:20:55,147
Silly, still using those tapes.

390
00:20:55,147 --> 00:20:57,547
Kogoro, hurry!

391
00:20:57,547 --> 00:20:58,947
Darn it!

392
00:21:00,547 --> 00:21:02,247
This is...

393
00:21:05,047 --> 00:21:06,247
What?

394
00:21:06,247 --> 00:21:09,547
As I thought, it was just a coincidence.

395
00:21:09,547 --> 00:21:11,347
How do you know?

396
00:21:11,347 --> 00:21:14,847
Mom! Wait up!

397
00:22:40,947 --> 00:22:43,247
It looks like Pop's back already.

398
00:22:43,247 --> 00:22:45,547
Oh, really? Who cares!

399
00:22:45,547 --> 00:22:47,547
Lewd old man!

400
00:22:49,647 --> 00:22:51,847
"Tonight's drinking party has been canceled!"

401
00:22:51,847 --> 00:22:54,447
"Sorry about that, Kogorou. - Poirot Master."

402
00:23:00,747 --> 00:23:02,047
I see.

403
00:23:02,047 --> 00:23:04,447
Since he'd used this strategy so often before,

404
00:23:04,447 --> 00:23:06,947
he saw throught it instantly.

405
00:23:06,947 --> 00:23:08,847
And he was able to find his own alibi tapes so quickly

406
00:23:08,847 --> 00:23:11,447
because he skipped on the party.

407
00:23:12,647 --> 00:23:18,147
Then, he tried to play it one more time over the last call, but...

408
00:23:18,147 --> 00:23:20,847
Kogoro, hurry!

409
00:23:20,847 --> 00:23:23,747
Next, we'll have a friend of the groom, Kogoro Mouri,

410
00:23:23,747 --> 00:23:24,747
give a congratulatory speech!

411
00:23:24,747 --> 00:23:26,347
Thank you!

412
00:23:27,847 --> 00:23:30,547
What a bad luck, recording that part

413
00:23:30,547 --> 00:23:32,447
and accidentally playing it as well.

414
00:23:32,447 --> 00:23:34,247
Yes, quite a pity!

415
00:23:34,247 --> 00:23:38,147
Eri! Don't be fooled!

416
00:23:38,147 --> 00:23:40,447
Do your best!

417
00:23:42,647 --> 00:23:44,447
You too, Pops!

418
00:23:51,047 --> 00:23:52,247
Because it's hard to believe that

419
00:23:52,247 --> 00:23:54,947
we're staking out accompanied by girl high school students

420
00:23:54,947 --> 00:23:58,247
and an elementary school child, right?

421
00:23:58,247 --> 00:24:00,247
That goes for Hammer man, too.

422
00:24:02,247 --> 00:24:03,247
It can't be...

423
00:24:03,247 --> 00:24:05,647
He's waiting to ambush us?

424
00:24:05,647 --> 00:24:06,847
No.

425
00:24:06,847 --> 00:24:10,647
I don't think he had any intention to ambush anybody.

